metadata.name: View From My Window #15
metadata.description:
Inspired by the grid-like patterns ever-present in residential windows, "View From My Window" distorts images generated with CLIP Guided Diffusion and rearranges them into random colorful grids.

<< 8 color palettes and endless configurations – Have fun! >>

Press s (when "open live" is active) to save a PNG image.

:)

metadata.name: abstract altitudes #3
metadata.description:
'abstract altitudes' is a modern take on an archaic aspect of nature: mountains. It is up to you to find the combination of shapes that form an appropriate ode to the beauty of the natural world.

4 palettes of varying rarities: neutral (40%), bold (30%), monochrome(20%), orchid (10%)


100% coded (using p5.js)

metadata.name: a day in the life #21
metadata.description:
'a day in the life' captures various perspectives of the same mountain range, tiled in uniquely interesting ways. Though it presents a minimal, abstract front, most elements are composed of thousands of small lines constrained by curves and shapes. 

Larger grids are rarer.
5 colour palettes of varying rarities inspired by nature (1 ultra rare palette: 'desert').

1000x1000
100% coded (using p5.js)

metadata.name: Strange Data #141
metadata.description:
"strange data" chaotic and disorienting visual  experience. 

It could feature unexpected patterns and anomalies, may challenge understanding of what is real or normal. 

It could also be described as a glitchy, or abstract representation of data, blurring the lines between the digital and physical worlds.
